=== Conventions Used in This Book

==== Typographical Conventions

The following typographical conventions are used in this book:

_Italic_ indicates new terms, URLs, email addresses, filenames, and file extensions.

`Constant width` is used for program listings, as well as within text to refer to program elements such as variable or function names, data types, statements, and keywords.

*`Constant width bold`* shows commands or other text that should be typed literally by the user.

_`Constant width italic`_ shows the text that should be replaced with user-supplied values.

==== Admonitions

Tips and tricks will be shown as:

TIP: This is a tip message.

When I'd like to inform you of danger, harm, or consequences that would exist:

WARNING: Danger Will Robinson!

Important callout information is indicated as:

IMPORTANT: I'm afraid I can't let you do that, Dave.

When I would like to advise you to act carefully...

CAUTION: You may crash and burn.

Something that may be useful at some point in time...

NOTE: This is a note.